story:
January 12, 2026

The sky finally fractured, spilling gems of frozen starlight across the valley. Today, the first true snow fell, and my heart soared with every swirling flake. I stood in the courtyard of the Frost-Spire, watching the crystals dancenot just as ice, but as tiny, glowing sigils of ancient mana. To see the snowflakes again is to witness a quiet miracle. Each one that landed on my palm hummed with a soft, melodic chill, pulsing like a tiny heartbeat. I feel weightless, drunk on the crisp air and the silver silence. Winter has arrived, and with it, a magic I thought long forgotten. I am truly, wildly happy.
